            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.07.00b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Weekly Times</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Answers to correspondents', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Weekly times</seg>, 18 July 1885, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Farmers gazette supplement</seg>, p. 1 (B85.07.09). It is introduced by <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">'</seg>
                     <seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Specimen of Tree</seg>
                     <seg style="">. — A D, Little River. — Baron von Mueller, to whom we submitted your specimen, returned the following reply: —'.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The specimen submitted is of an Australian <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>, but as neither flowers nor fruits are on the branches, it will not be safe to name the species. What looks like a fruit is a gall. Such galls are useful for dye and tan, as shown by me in the exhibition of 1867</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Intercolonial Exhibition of Australasia, Melbourne, 1866-7.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> I already.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>
               </seg>
            </p>
